#X text 65 32 More complex carriar and/or modulator signals will create more partials in any Amplitude Modulation (and Ring Modulation) patch. For a sawtooth wave modulated by a sine wave we get side partials for each component of the sine wave. We usually see just sine waves as the modulator signal because that is probably just enough \, specially as an effects processor \, but we can go crazy and try other things., f 50;
#X text 65 170 A more interesting and widely adopted synthesis technique to generating complex sounds is via frequency/phase modulation \, as we'll see next. We can use a similar principle though \, which is using frequencies with a harmonic relationship \, sligthly detuned \, to also generate harmonic spectra. Here we have the modulation frequency at a detuned fifth below (0.667)., f 50;
#N canvas 280 227 368 208 plot 0;
#X obj 33 21 inlet~;
#X obj 33 56 rfft~;
#X obj 80 60 block~ 4096;
#X obj 33 94 mag~;
